19
00:01:02.997 --> 00:01:03.932
APD. stop!

20
00:01:07.467 --> 00:01:09.202
You got the wrong guy!

21
00:01:21.049 --> 00:01:22.115
Get off of me.

22
00:01:22.249 --> 00:01:23.818
-I didn't do anything.
-Yeah?

23
00:01:23.952 --> 00:01:25.587
Well. I got an eyewitness who
saw you running from the scene.

24
00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:29.122
-You're under arrest.
-It wasn't me. It wasn't me.

25
00:01:30.925 --> 00:01:32.760
Relax!

26
00:01:32.894 --> 00:01:35.063
<i>The state</i>
<i>of Georgia is preparing</i>

27
00:01:35.195 --> 00:01:39.399
<i>to execute death row inmate</i>
<i>George Long in less than</i>
<i>ten hours.</i>

28
00:01:39.534 --> 00:01:43.905
Long. who has maintained
his innocence.
was found guilty of murdering

29
00:01:44.038 --> 00:01:49.611
Atlanta real estate developer
Thomas Kelly and his wife
Marjorie in 2010.

30
00:01:49.744 --> 00:01:52.780
<i>Long. who previously</i>
<i>served time for armed robbery.</i>

31
00:01:52.914 --> 00:01:56.183
<i>shot the Kellys</i>
<i>during a failed carjacking.</i>

32
00:01:56.851 --> 00:01:58.920
<i>We have other top</i>
<i>stories to get to...</i>

33
00:01:59.053 --> 00:02:02.657
I left early. but Atlanta
traffic took that as
a challenge.

34
00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:04.659
You look great.

35
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:06.728
Thanks. you too.

36
00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:10.497
-Everything okay?
-Of course.

37
00:02:10.632 --> 00:02:12.767
-Just happy you're here.
-Ah.

38
00:02:14.334 --> 00:02:16.136
-All right.
-Let's go to your place.

39
00:02:16.269 --> 00:02:19.373
What. right now?
I thought we'd get dinner.
I made a reservation.

40
00:02:19.507 --> 00:02:22.142
Oh. come on. Will.
I've missed you.

41
00:02:22.275 --> 00:02:25.212
Besides. when's the last time
you did anything spontaneous?

42
00:02:25.345 --> 00:02:26.648
Hmm. Last night.

43
00:02:26.781 --> 00:02:28.549
I microwaved spaghetti
without a lid on it.

44
00:02:28.683 --> 00:02:29.784
Huh.

45
00:02:31.385 --> 00:02:33.888
I see your point. After you.

46
00:02:37.592 --> 00:02:41.194
... <i>checking in</i>
<i>with our very own Sandra Jones</i>
<i>in Cobb County</i>

47
00:02:41.328 --> 00:02:42.930
<i>who can't wait to tell us more.</i>

48
00:02:44.966 --> 00:02:46.734
So. um. how was New York?

49
00:02:46.868 --> 00:02:50.170
It was great.
Bought a latte for $16.

50
00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:51.739
Wow. good deal. huh?

51
00:02:51.873 --> 00:02:52.840
I know. How about you?

52
00:02:53.273 --> 00:02:55.877
Betty has a new shampoo.
She smells like grapefruit.

53
00:02:56.010 --> 00:02:58.211
- How's that
for spontaneous. huh?

54
00:02:58.345 --> 00:03:01.516
So. you want to tell me about
the guy in the baseball hat
following us?

55
00:03:02.016 --> 00:03:03.084
No idea. Never seen him.

56
00:03:03.651 --> 00:03:05.352
Okay. I'll find out myself.

57
00:03:05.753 --> 00:03:08.022
No. He's been
following me all day.

58
00:03:08.790 --> 00:03:11.291
-Okay. Turn left here.
-Oh.

59
00:03:18.265 --> 00:03:21.803
Hey. You see this lady here?
She's not interested.

60
00:03:21.936 --> 00:03:23.638
Yo. it's not
what it looks like.

61
00:03:23.771 --> 00:03:27.474
My name is Brett Fontaine. I'm
a retired cop. Check my pocket.

62
00:03:28.176 --> 00:03:29.744
Oh.

63
00:03:31.344 --> 00:03:33.514
Yep.

64
00:03:37.618 --> 00:03:40.454
NYPD? Why are you in Atlanta?

65
00:03:41.388 --> 00:03:44.324
Because your friend stole
something from Ron Moffitino.

66
00:03:44.458 --> 00:03:46.527
and Ron Moffitino
hired me to get it back.

67
00:03:46.661 --> 00:03:48.062
I don't know a Ron Moffitino.

68
00:03:48.196 --> 00:03:49.964
Ooh. and you're
lying. Ava Green.

69
00:03:50.098 --> 00:03:53.935
Ron Moffitino
is an interior decorator.
and you stole his urn.

70
00:03:54.068 --> 00:03:56.336
All right. Everyone
stop saying Ron Moffitino.

71
00:03:57.270 --> 00:03:58.773
You stole an urn?

72
00:03:59.507 --> 00:04:00.742
Whose urn?

73
00:04:01.976 --> 00:04:03.010
Meat Loaf.

74
00:04:03.578 --> 00:04:05.880
-The singer?
-Singer and actor.

75
00:04:06.514 --> 00:04:08.381
also known as Marvin Lee Aday.

76
00:04:08.516 --> 00:04:12.553
And Ron Moffitino wants the urn
and his ashes back by
midnight. or else.

77
00:04:12.687 --> 00:04:14.287
Okay. no more full names.

78
00:04:14.956 --> 00:04:18.291
-Ava. just give
the nice man his urn.
-Yeah.

79
00:04:18.693 --> 00:04:20.427
It's not that simple.

80
00:04:20.561 --> 00:04:21.696
Why is it not that simple?

81
00:04:21.829 --> 00:04:23.831
Whoa. whoa.
Do you not have the urn?

82
00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:28.435
Okay. look.
We're good. all right?

83
00:04:28.569 --> 00:04:29.737
I'll take it from here.

84
00:04:30.403 --> 00:04:32.707
I'll get him back his urn. and
if he has a problem with it.

85
00:04:32.840 --> 00:04:34.575
Ron can come find me himself.

86
00:04:36.177 --> 00:04:37.645
Okay. And what's your name?

87
00:04:38.813 --> 00:04:40.581
Special Agent Will Trent.

88
00:04:41.082 --> 00:04:42.717
Okay. Special Agent Will Trent.

89
00:04:42.850 --> 00:04:46.087
I'll tell Ron Moffitino
that you and Ava Green--

90
00:04:46.220 --> 00:04:47.688
Just get out of here.

91
00:04:50.258 --> 00:04:52.026
-I can explain.
-Mmm.

92
00:04:52.560 --> 00:04:53.795
Can't wait.

93
00:05:03.538 --> 00:05:05.405
Let's go. Get it together.

94
00:05:06.339 --> 00:05:07.708
- Okay.
- Come on.

95
00:05:08.209 --> 00:05:12.345
Excuse me. I am looking
for Detective Michael Ormewood.
It's urgent.

96
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:15.283
Hey. Right here. You don't have
to yell it. Can I help you?

97
00:05:15.415 --> 00:05:18.119
You were the responding officer
in the George Long case.

98
00:05:18.653 --> 00:05:19.921
-Yes?
-I'm sorry. who are you?

99
00:05:20.054 --> 00:05:22.023
Joanne Drexel. I'm part
of George's legal team.

100
00:05:22.156 --> 00:05:24.125
Tell them. Tell them
exactly what you told me.

101
00:05:24.258 --> 00:05:26.093
What is this? What's going on?

102
00:05:26.227 --> 00:05:27.161
You don't remember me?

103
00:05:27.295 --> 00:05:28.729
I... Should I?

104
00:05:29.263 --> 00:05:30.731
I'm the witness.

105
00:05:32.365 --> 00:05:33.634
I told you I saw George.

106
00:05:33.768 --> 00:05:35.503
Keep going. Tell him.

107
00:05:36.237 --> 00:05:37.972
I lied.

108
00:05:41.175 --> 00:05:44.212
-I made it all up.
-Wait. What are you saying
right now?

109
00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:46.047
George Long is innocent.

110
00:05:47.615 --> 00:05:51.519
We have nine hours
until he dies. We need
to stop his execution.

111
00:06:06.567 --> 00:06:08.536
You're judging me.
I can feel it.

112
00:06:08.669 --> 00:06:11.038
I just have questions. is all.

113
00:06:12.807 --> 00:06:16.443
Ron Moffitino hired me
to take photos of this place
that he just worked on.

114
00:06:16.577 --> 00:06:19.479
Guy's a bit sketchy. Probably
should have turned it down.

115
00:06:19.614 --> 00:06:22.583
But it was 1.500 bucks.
Who am I to say no?

116
00:06:22.717 --> 00:06:25.019
Then guess what?
Ron stiffed me.

117
00:06:25.753 --> 00:06:28.455
So. naturally.
you stole Meat Loaf's ashes?

118
00:06:28.589 --> 00:06:31.692
I had to look out for myself.
okay? $1.500 is a lot of money.

119
00:06:31.826 --> 00:06:33.661
-It's rent.
-Have you heard
of small claims court?

120
00:06:33.794 --> 00:06:36.797
Have you heard of
living your life in the moment?

121
00:06:37.497 --> 00:06:39.166
This is who I am.

122
00:06:39.300 --> 00:06:42.837
It may not always be easy.
but it's way more fun.

123
00:06:44.338 --> 00:06:47.942
You're responsible.
You're conscientious.
You're predictable.

124
00:06:48.075 --> 00:06:49.977
You have no idea what
it's like to have to hustle.

125
00:06:50.111 --> 00:06:53.681
Okay. hang on a second. I've
had to hustle my entire life.

126
00:06:53.814 --> 00:06:55.983
I've sold stolen rugs
out of a van.

127
00:06:56.117 --> 00:06:59.987
I basically cheated
my way through school.
and most importantly.

128
00:07:00.521 --> 00:07:02.323
I love Meat Loaf. Huge fan.

129
00:07:02.757 --> 00:07:04.625
-You're not serious.
-Dead serious.

130
00:07:04.759 --> 00:07:06.459
You know what?
I'm gonna help you.

131
00:07:07.028 --> 00:07:08.896
-Where's the urn now?
-I pawned it.

132
00:07:09.030 --> 00:07:11.165
Excellent.
At least we know where it is.

133
00:07:11.299 --> 00:07:13.134
First. we need an ATM.

134
00:07:14.535 --> 00:07:16.404
Eduardo. who's Meat Loaf?

135
00:07:16.537 --> 00:07:18.239
- <i>Meat Loaf was a singer...</i>
-You lied. I knew it.

136
00:07:18.372 --> 00:07:20.574
You want a hustler? You got
one. Just try to keep up.

137
00:07:20.708 --> 00:07:23.811
...Bat Out of Hell
<i>has sold over 40 million</i>
<i>copies worldwide</i>

138
00:07:23.945 --> 00:07:27.114
<i>and is the fourth best-selling</i>
<i>album in history. Meat Loaf...</i>

139
00:07:28.316 --> 00:07:32.186
Okay. Harris. why don't
you tell us what really
happened 15 years ago?

140
00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:34.922
I went to get Chinese food.

141
00:07:35.589 --> 00:07:37.490
I was walking back to my car

142
00:07:37.625 --> 00:07:43.230
and I heard the gunshots from
the parking garage across
the street.

143
00:07:44.398 --> 00:07:49.469
And I was trying to get out of
there. and then you showed up
and you started

144
00:07:49.603 --> 00:07:52.740
-asking me a lot of questions--
-I asked you if you saw
anything.

145
00:07:52.873 --> 00:07:54.241
You described George Long.

146
00:07:54.375 --> 00:07:56.711
You said he ran out of
the garage like he was fleeing.

147
00:07:56.844 --> 00:07:59.780
I know. I. uh... I lied.

148
00:07:59.914 --> 00:08:01.782
I saw him.

149
00:08:01.916 --> 00:08:06.120
I saw him. but he wasn't
leaving the garage.

150
00:08:06.253 --> 00:08:09.090
He was just walking
down the street.

151
00:08:09.223 --> 00:08:11.491
Why would you do that?
Why would you make that up?

152
00:08:11.625 --> 00:08:13.995
He was yelling. okay? He was...

153
00:08:14.128 --> 00:08:17.497
You were yelling and you got
in my face. and it was scary--

154
00:08:17.631 --> 00:08:20.334
Hey. hey! Don't you try
to pin this on me. okay?

155
00:08:20.468 --> 00:08:23.004
You showed up here days
after George was arrested.

156
00:08:23.137 --> 00:08:25.206
You ID'd him. Why didn't
you say something then. huh?

157
00:08:25.339 --> 00:08:28.642
I know. I think
about it every day. okay?

158
00:08:28.776 --> 00:08:30.578
It just got so big.

159
00:08:30.711 --> 00:08:32.813
I'm sorry! I just...

160
00:08:34.415 --> 00:08:35.616
You want to take a walk?

161
00:08:36.217 --> 00:08:37.551
No. I'm fine right here.

162
00:08:37.685 --> 00:08:39.387
All right. listen. Even if
this man is telling the truth.

163
00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:41.288
he's too drunk to
take a statement right now.

164
00:08:41.422 --> 00:08:43.724
By the way. I find this whole
thing pretty damn convenient.

165
00:08:43.858 --> 00:08:46.060
How do we know he didn't come
up with that story after
you bought him a few drinks?

166
00:08:46.193 --> 00:08:48.529
That sounds like it's right
out of the APD's playbook.

167
00:08:48.662 --> 00:08:52.299
Hey. I'm just saying.
give me one reason why I should
believe him.

168
00:08:53.467 --> 00:08:57.671
Because George Long is about
to be murdered by the state
of Georgia.

169
00:09:00.741 --> 00:09:02.076
I'm sorry.

170
00:09:03.644 --> 00:09:06.881
I'm sorry.

171
00:09:10.418 --> 00:09:14.822
Hey. All right. let's take
a second. Let's talk about it.

172
00:09:14.955 --> 00:09:16.525
The key witness lied.

173
00:09:16.657 --> 00:09:18.059
What are
you gonna do about this?

174
00:09:18.859 --> 00:09:21.695
Nothing. George Long
was convicted by a jury.

175
00:09:21.829 --> 00:09:24.098
The guy's had three appeals.
He's not my problem.

176
00:09:24.231 --> 00:09:27.502
Yeah. I know. He actually
did you a lot of good.

177
00:09:28.035 --> 00:09:30.037
-What the hell does that mean?
-I did my research.

178
00:09:30.171 --> 00:09:32.773
You got promoted to detective
right after he was sentenced.

179
00:09:32.907 --> 00:09:34.241
You owe him your career.

180
00:09:34.375 --> 00:09:36.177
All right. that's enough.
Are we done here?

181
00:09:36.310 --> 00:09:39.580
Sure. I'm just gonna
file a last-minute appeal

182
00:09:39.713 --> 00:09:43.050
that'll probably end up
in somebody's shredder.
but you two sleep tight.

183
00:09:44.018 --> 00:09:46.253
Try not to intimidate
anyone on the way home.

184
00:09:49.690 --> 00:09:50.991
You all right?

185
00:09:52.226 --> 00:09:54.161
I want to see
those damn case files.

186
00:10:00.301 --> 00:10:02.369
- Urn lady.
- Hi.

187
00:10:02.504 --> 00:10:03.737
Welcome back.

188
00:10:03.871 --> 00:10:05.840
I've made a big mistake.
I came in earlier.

189
00:10:05.973 --> 00:10:07.975
I wasn't thinking.
I'm a huge idiot.

190
00:10:08.109 --> 00:10:10.711
Oh. babe. don't beat yourself
up. We'll make it right.

191
00:10:11.445 --> 00:10:15.416
My girlfriend sold
you Meat Loaf's urn.
and I need to buy it back.

192
00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:17.384
I wish.

193
00:10:17.519 --> 00:10:20.354
That baby flew off my shelves
like a bat out of hell.

194
00:10:20.488 --> 00:10:22.189
You've already sold it?

195
00:10:22.323 --> 00:10:25.793
Sure did. Put it on the website
and one of my regulars
snatched it up.

196
00:10:25.926 --> 00:10:27.728
Folks in New York City
were calling too.

197
00:10:27.862 --> 00:10:31.632
You would not believe
the money they were offering
for that urn.

198
00:10:32.766 --> 00:10:37.204
I wish I could have kept
her myself. but. uh.
times are tough. so...

199
00:10:37.338 --> 00:10:40.575
Would you be able to give
us the name of the guy
who bought the urn?

200
00:10:41.142 --> 00:10:42.743
Sorry. darling.
I cannot do that.

201
00:10:42.877 --> 00:10:44.345
Let me ask you. you a fan?

202
00:10:45.946 --> 00:10:47.516
Certified Meat Lover. brother.

203
00:10:48.249 --> 00:10:51.752
Oh. man. Look.
I... I really need this urn.

204
00:10:52.386 --> 00:10:54.623
Without Meat Loaf.
I wouldn't even be here today.

205
00:10:55.222 --> 00:10:57.758
My parents. they met
at a show in New Haven.

206
00:10:58.492 --> 00:11:01.028
-small venue
called Toad's Place.
-Toad's Place.

207
00:11:01.695 --> 00:11:03.430
-Historic.
-That's right.

208
00:11:04.533 --> 00:11:05.799
Which show?

209
00:11:08.202 --> 00:11:10.871
<i>Dead Ringer.</i> October 1981.

210
00:11:12.106 --> 00:11:13.508
- Classic. classic.
- Mmm.

211
00:11:15.510 --> 00:11:18.279
His mum used to talk about it
all the time. Didn't she?

212
00:11:18.412 --> 00:11:20.080
-Yeah. Oh...
-God rest her soul.

213
00:11:20.214 --> 00:11:22.316
You know. she was
working at the bar.

214
00:11:22.449 --> 00:11:25.352
My old man came in and bought
a drink. and. well.
the rest is history.

215
00:11:26.153 --> 00:11:29.356
They called
it loaf at first sight.

216
00:11:31.593 --> 00:11:33.060
It was a meat-cute.

217
00:11:33.194 --> 00:11:34.195
M-E-A-T.

218
00:11:34.328 --> 00:11:36.096
-There you go. Uh-huh.
-There it is.

219
00:11:36.230 --> 00:11:38.265
- Okay. That's good.
That's good too.
- Yeah.

220
00:11:39.333 --> 00:11:40.434
What do you say?

221
00:11:41.603 --> 00:11:42.836
Screw it.

222
00:11:42.970 --> 00:11:44.872
- I'm a hopeless romantic. so...
- Aw.

223
00:11:46.006 --> 00:11:50.144
His name is Murph Sanchez.

224
00:11:50.277 --> 00:11:52.647
Actually. he's having
a little shindig tonight.

225
00:11:52.780 --> 00:11:55.249
- Love it. Sounds fun.
- Mm-hmm.

226
00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:58.553
Now. um... Just
between you and me.

227
00:11:59.220 --> 00:12:00.955
this guy can be a real a-hole.

228
00:12:01.722 --> 00:12:04.225
Understood. Meat Lover.

229
00:12:05.594 --> 00:12:07.662
My man. Bye. y'all.

230
00:12:07.795 --> 00:12:09.163
Let's go pay
Murph Sanchez a visit.

231
00:12:09.296 --> 00:12:11.700
That was awesome.
Now we get to crash a party.

232
00:12:11.832 --> 00:12:13.334
Oh.

233
00:12:15.035 --> 00:12:16.270
Uh...

234
00:12:18.239 --> 00:12:19.873
You know what? After you.

235
00:12:20.007 --> 00:12:21.509
That's what I thought.

236
00:12:24.945 --> 00:12:26.046
Ex-boyfriend?

237
00:12:26.180 --> 00:12:28.550
Who do you think I am?

238
00:12:29.250 --> 00:12:30.851
Have you been
through these yet?

239
00:12:31.452 --> 00:12:33.787
-No. I'm still
on court transcripts.
-Okay.

240
00:12:34.321 --> 00:12:36.757
Hey. I was going to
get a burrito. Wanna go?

241
00:12:36.890 --> 00:12:38.859
I can't.
It's gonna be a long night.

242
00:12:38.993 --> 00:12:40.794
I'll just go by myself.

243
00:12:40.928 --> 00:12:44.164
because that's how
I'm going to die anyway.
alone with a broken heart.

244
00:12:44.733 --> 00:12:46.066
George Long. What's this?

245
00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:47.868
Please stick around.
We could use your brain.

246
00:12:48.002 --> 00:12:49.704
Well. it depends
on what you're doing.

247
00:12:49.837 --> 00:12:52.741
I'm making sure
George Long's guilty
before he's put to death.

248
00:12:52.873 --> 00:12:54.108
We had a witness recant.

249
00:12:54.676 --> 00:12:56.910
Okay. perspective.

250
00:12:58.713 --> 00:12:59.847
Give me the SparkNotes.

251
00:13:00.281 --> 00:13:02.049
Prior to murdering the Kellys.

252
00:13:02.182 --> 00:13:04.018
George Long spent six years
in federal prison

253
00:13:04.151 --> 00:13:05.687
for sticking up a car wash
at gunpoint.

254
00:13:05.853 --> 00:13:07.722
Violent criminal history.
got it.

255
00:13:07.855 --> 00:13:10.190
And when I cuffed him. I found
a wad of cash in his pocket.

256
00:13:10.324 --> 00:13:12.594
which the prosecution suggested
he stole from Marjorie Kelly.

257
00:13:12.727 --> 00:13:16.531
However. forensics didn't find
his fingerprints on anything.

258
00:13:16.665 --> 00:13:19.333
-Her wallet.
her purse. their car.
-What about the murder weapon?

259
00:13:19.466 --> 00:13:20.635
The gun was never found.

260
00:13:21.670 --> 00:13:24.938
It's a lot of circumstantial
evidence. Who worked the case?

261
00:13:25.072 --> 00:13:26.006
Ernie Pyzeck.

262
00:13:26.140 --> 00:13:28.409
Home-by.

263
00:13:29.410 --> 00:13:31.845
Hey. Pyzeck taught me a ton.
He was a great detective.

264
00:13:31.979 --> 00:13:35.416
Yeah. as long as
he was home by dinner.

265
00:13:36.250 --> 00:13:37.851
What do you think. Angie?

266
00:13:37.985 --> 00:13:40.888
Honestly. there were a lot of
people that hated the victim.

267
00:13:41.021 --> 00:13:43.190
Tom Kelly. big bad
real estate developer.

268
00:13:43.591 --> 00:13:48.429
Check this out.
Autopsy report. See his ribs?

269
00:13:48.896 --> 00:13:50.230
Bruises.

270
00:13:50.364 --> 00:13:51.999
Yeah. the ME suggested
those were a week old.

271
00:13:52.132 --> 00:13:53.702
Say he got in a fight...

272
00:13:53.834 --> 00:13:56.538
Whoever gave him those bruises
came back to finish the job.

273
00:13:57.237 --> 00:13:59.406
Looks like he was kicked.
Maybe with the toe of a boot.

274
00:13:59.541 --> 00:14:01.942
Did George Long have any
connection with the Kellys?

275
00:14:02.544 --> 00:14:03.745
-None.
-Huh.

276
00:14:03.877 --> 00:14:05.680
It looks pretty personal to me.

277
00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:07.582
Why didn't they bring
this up in the trial?

278
00:14:07.716 --> 00:14:10.150
I'm gonna try and find somebody
who was close with the Kellys.

279
00:14:10.284 --> 00:14:11.619
help us fill in
some of these blanks.

280
00:14:11.753 --> 00:14:13.788
How much time do
we have before Long's executed?

281
00:14:13.921 --> 00:14:15.155
Less than seven hours.

282
00:14:20.861 --> 00:14:22.764
You've got 20 minutes.

283
00:14:22.896 --> 00:14:27.267
I'm getting dim sum with a man
who has no kids and a full
head of hair.

284
00:14:27.401 --> 00:14:29.436
Oh. Good for you.
We won't keep you from that.

285
00:14:29.571 --> 00:14:32.607
So. you were Tom Kelly's
assistant at the time of
his murder. is that right?

286
00:14:32.741 --> 00:14:34.341
Yeah. for over a decade.

287
00:14:34.475 --> 00:14:37.344
Not to speak ill of the dead.
but he was a piece of garbage.

288
00:14:38.780 --> 00:14:39.947
What's this about?

289
00:14:40.347 --> 00:14:42.249
Well. we're trying to
make sure we got the right guy.

290
00:14:42.383 --> 00:14:44.318
You think
you got the wrong guy?

291
00:14:44.451 --> 00:14:47.121
I mean. isn't he
getting executed tonight?

292
00:14:47.254 --> 00:14:49.189
-You're cutting
it pretty close.
-Yep.

293
00:14:49.323 --> 00:14:51.325
So. around
the time of his murder.

294
00:14:51.458 --> 00:14:53.994
do you recall if there were
any residents that were
particularly angry with him?

295
00:14:54.128 --> 00:14:59.032
Too many. Tom was always
throwing people out of
their homes.

296
00:14:59.166 --> 00:15:01.636
-Did any of them
ever get physical?
-Oh. yeah.

297
00:15:02.469 --> 00:15:03.805
I remember one.

298
00:15:04.706 --> 00:15:06.708
Maybe like a week
before the shooting.

299
00:15:07.174 --> 00:15:09.711
Guy stormed in because
his girlfriend got evicted.

300
00:15:09.844 --> 00:15:14.047
He got Tom on the ground
and started kicking him
and kicking him.

301
00:15:14.181 --> 00:15:16.984
and. I mean. security
had to carry him out.

302
00:15:18.252 --> 00:15:20.454
-You remember his name?
-Mm-mmm.

303
00:15:20.588 --> 00:15:23.323
-His girlfriend's name?
-Had you ever seen him before?

304
00:15:23.858 --> 00:15:25.660
This was 15 years ago.

305
00:15:25.794 --> 00:15:28.462
-Is there any record of this?
-Tom didn't want
to press charges.

306
00:15:28.596 --> 00:15:31.633
and the guy kept telling me
he wanted to kill him too.

307
00:15:31.766 --> 00:15:33.467
It got real ugly.

308
00:15:33.601 --> 00:15:35.637
And you didn't even think
to mention this
to Detective Pyzeck

309
00:15:35.770 --> 00:15:38.071
or anyone else
during the investigation?

310
00:15:38.873 --> 00:15:40.107
No one asked.

311
00:15:47.981 --> 00:15:52.787
So Murph Sanchez is
having a white party. Perfect.

312
00:15:52.921 --> 00:15:55.222
Yeah. um... It's okay.

313
00:15:55.355 --> 00:15:57.224
-Mm-hmm.
-Let's just keep it simple.

314
00:15:57.357 --> 00:16:01.028
We'll find Murph. buy back
the urn. and then I'm taking
you to dinner.

315
00:16:02.429 --> 00:16:04.097
Who the hell
are you two clowns?

316
00:16:05.834 --> 00:16:06.935
Get out of my house.

317
00:16:07.067 --> 00:16:09.102
You must be Murph.

318
00:16:09.236 --> 00:16:10.872
-Yeah.
-Um...

319
00:16:11.004 --> 00:16:12.674
We are a. uh...

320
00:16:12.807 --> 00:16:16.678
a gift from one of
your many generous friends.

321
00:16:16.811 --> 00:16:18.613
We're working the party.

322
00:16:18.746 --> 00:16:24.384
I'm a magician. and this is
my lovely assistant.
the Amazing Ava.

323
00:16:25.252 --> 00:16:29.256
Okay. Do something. Impress me.

324
00:16:30.390 --> 00:16:31.425
Oh.

325
00:16:34.963 --> 00:16:36.764
-This your watch?
-Ta-da!

326
00:16:40.902 --> 00:16:42.336
That's pretty neat.

327
00:16:43.838 --> 00:16:46.608
Okay. Go dazzle them.

328
00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:49.009
But if you pocket anything.

329
00:16:49.978 --> 00:16:51.411
we'll have a problem.

330
00:16:54.147 --> 00:16:55.683
-Swell guy.
-Hmm.

331
00:16:57.184 --> 00:16:58.853
When did you learn close magic?

332
00:16:58.987 --> 00:17:02.022
- Oh. I have plenty more
up my sleeve.

333
00:17:04.024 --> 00:17:07.595
Brother. every person on that
jury said George was guilty.

334
00:17:07.729 --> 00:17:08.963
Yeah. you're right.

335
00:17:09.096 --> 00:17:12.232
We had an eyewitness
point us directly at an ex-con

336
00:17:12.366 --> 00:17:14.002
who just so happened
to be leaving the garage

337
00:17:14.134 --> 00:17:17.572
at the exact same time
the two rich folks got popped.

338
00:17:17.705 --> 00:17:19.541
Perp had a wad of cash
on him. right?

339
00:17:19.941 --> 00:17:22.175
Ain't a smoking
gun. but it's pretty good.

340
00:17:22.309 --> 00:17:25.513
Yeah. but Pyzeck.
without a witness.
the whole thing falls apart.

341
00:17:25.647 --> 00:17:30.417
Hey. God put our eyes
looking this way for a reason.

342
00:17:31.753 --> 00:17:32.720
Yeah. I guess I just...

343
00:17:33.253 --> 00:17:35.389
I just want to know that I did
the right thing. you know?

344
00:17:35.523 --> 00:17:37.959
Of course you did.
You didn't convict the guy.

345
00:17:38.091 --> 00:17:41.461
You didn't sentence him.
and you're not putting
the needle in his arm.

346
00:17:42.229 --> 00:17:44.732
This ain't on you. Ormy.
Just let it go.

347
00:17:45.833 --> 00:17:47.134
I'm trying.

348
00:17:50.838 --> 00:17:52.740
You know what case
I think about?

349
00:17:54.709 --> 00:17:55.810
None of them.

350
00:17:58.378 --> 00:17:59.614
Hey. you know. uh.

351
00:18:00.113 --> 00:18:02.482
Tom Kelly's assistant said
that a week before the murder.

352
00:18:02.617 --> 00:18:04.686
some guy came into their
office. knocked Tom around.

353
00:18:04.819 --> 00:18:07.120
-threatened to kill him.
-Oh. yeah?

354
00:18:07.789 --> 00:18:09.156
-Yeah.
-Hmm.

355
00:18:09.958 --> 00:18:11.425
Why didn't you question her?

356
00:18:11.960 --> 00:18:13.193
Didn't need to.

357
00:18:13.795 --> 00:18:15.162
We already had our guy.

358
00:18:24.271 --> 00:18:25.974
Ma'am. I need help.

359
00:18:26.608 --> 00:18:28.108
Can it wait till tomorrow?

360
00:18:28.241 --> 00:18:30.578
No. George Long is going
to be executed in four hours.

361
00:18:30.712 --> 00:18:32.580
and I think
he might be innocent.

362
00:18:33.514 --> 00:18:36.483
I've worked capital cases
in my career. They're heavy.

363
00:18:36.618 --> 00:18:40.021
But we got new information.
okay? The case against him.
it doesn't hold up.

364
00:18:40.153 --> 00:18:42.991
Okay. I just-- I need time.
I need time to get the evidence
that I need--

365
00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:46.393
Listen. listen. it's not that
simple. There's a system--

366
00:18:46.527 --> 00:18:48.896
Oh. my God. I'm so sick
of everyone blaming the system!

367
00:18:49.030 --> 00:18:52.667
Guess what. Amanda?
We are the system. okay?

368
00:18:52.800 --> 00:18:56.504
So if the system sucks or the
system's broken. that's on us!

369
00:18:58.806 --> 00:19:01.441
I don't know
who you think you are.

370
00:19:02.010 --> 00:19:05.278
coming up into my office.
raising your voice at me.

371
00:19:06.748 --> 00:19:11.919
But you will never do that
again. Do I make myself clear?

372
00:19:13.353 --> 00:19:14.622
Yeah.

373
00:19:14.756 --> 00:19:15.857
Good.

374
00:19:18.325 --> 00:19:19.594
Now.

375
00:19:20.460 --> 00:19:21.829
what do you need?

376
00:19:33.440 --> 00:19:34.909
Are they on drugs or am I?

377
00:19:35.043 --> 00:19:38.311
It's a silent disco.
Do you see the headsets?

378
00:19:38.445 --> 00:19:40.615
They're all synced up
to the same playlist.

379
00:19:40.748 --> 00:19:42.850
-Then why are you whispering?
-I'm not sure.

380
00:19:47.021 --> 00:19:48.790
What music do you think
they're listening to?

381
00:19:54.796 --> 00:19:56.430
I think it's "Shout"
by the Isley Brothers.

382
00:19:56.564 --> 00:19:58.032
You really are
the world's best detective.

383
00:19:58.166 --> 00:19:59.399
-Thank you.
-Mmm.

384
00:20:02.737 --> 00:20:04.105
Tell me that's Meat Loaf's urn.

385
00:20:04.237 --> 00:20:06.406
Yes! That's Meat Loaf's urn.

386
00:20:06.541 --> 00:20:07.875
All right.

387
00:20:16.117 --> 00:20:19.520
Look. I'm being spontaneous.
Whoo!

388
00:20:21.354 --> 00:20:22.824
You come here often?

389
00:20:26.226 --> 00:20:27.929
Oh. yeah. I see you.

390
00:20:30.263 --> 00:20:32.967
Don't shout. Maybe shout.

391
00:20:33.735 --> 00:20:34.969
And shout.

392
00:20:37.404 --> 00:20:38.740
Oh.

393
00:20:42.110 --> 00:20:43.077
You good?

394
00:20:43.211 --> 00:20:44.579
I'm great.

395
00:20:48.381 --> 00:20:49.717
Now's our chance.

396
00:20:56.090 --> 00:20:58.626
-What are you doing?
-I'm not stealing.

397
00:20:59.093 --> 00:21:00.762
We're gonna pay what we owe.

398
00:21:00.895 --> 00:21:02.964
-You know. spontaneous.
but conscientious.
-Right. Excellent.

399
00:21:03.097 --> 00:21:04.732
Okay. I got it. Let's go.

400
00:21:05.398 --> 00:21:06.433
Oh.

401
00:21:06.834 --> 00:21:08.401
Murph Sanchez. twelve o'clock.

402
00:21:18.079 --> 00:21:19.479
I can't look away.

403
00:21:19.847 --> 00:21:20.948
Follow me.

404
00:21:24.152 --> 00:21:27.255
Watch the urn. Watch the urn.

405
00:21:36.030 --> 00:21:38.533
What's happening?

406
00:21:38.666 --> 00:21:41.169
I don't know.

407
00:21:41.301 --> 00:21:43.938
Put the urn down now!

408
00:21:44.505 --> 00:21:45.907
Murph. I can explain.

409
00:21:46.841 --> 00:21:48.142
What?

410
00:21:48.276 --> 00:21:50.745
Headset. I can explain.

411
00:21:50.878 --> 00:21:53.346
Save your breath.
Call the police. honeybun.

412
00:21:56.150 --> 00:21:58.553
Get out of the way.
Move. I said move.

413
00:21:58.686 --> 00:22:00.855
Okay. You run.
I'll take care of him.

414
00:22:02.422 --> 00:22:03.925
Don't you move. Houdini!

415
00:22:04.457 --> 00:22:06.127
Get out of my way.
I'm trying to...

416
00:22:08.495 --> 00:22:12.465
I told you
we'd have a problem...
Get out of my way! Move!

417
00:22:12.934 --> 00:22:13.935
I said move!

418
00:22:14.068 --> 00:22:15.102
He can't hear me.

419
00:22:15.236 --> 00:22:17.705
-Will. hurry!
-Ava. watch out!

420
00:22:19.472 --> 00:22:20.942
Give me the urn. sweetheart.

421
00:22:34.622 --> 00:22:36.290
Ava. let's go. Come on.

422
00:22:40.460 --> 00:22:41.829
I kicked him. Did you see?

423
00:22:41.963 --> 00:22:44.699
-I did. We gotta go. Now.
-This is our ride.

424
00:22:45.833 --> 00:22:47.902
-What? Why?
-I called it
when we were inside.

425
00:22:48.035 --> 00:22:51.072
I figured meat stick got
your plates at the pawn shop.
Come on.

426
00:22:52.139 --> 00:22:53.341
Brilliant. Okay.

427
00:22:53.774 --> 00:22:55.408
Okay.

428
00:22:55.910 --> 00:22:57.879
Okay. come on.
hurry up. drive. drive.

429
00:22:58.012 --> 00:22:58.980
Will...

430
00:22:59.113 --> 00:23:00.314
What?

431
00:23:00.748 --> 00:23:02.382
<i>Please</i>
<i>buckle your safety belts.</i>

432
00:23:02.516 --> 00:23:03.751
Whoa.

433
00:23:09.790 --> 00:23:12.459
Okay. that was insane.

434
00:23:12.593 --> 00:23:13.928
Completely insane.

435
00:23:14.061 --> 00:23:17.531
-You were amazing. So sexy.
-Yeah?

436
00:23:17.665 --> 00:23:19.700
Oh. Thank you.

437
00:23:19.834 --> 00:23:22.570
Oh. um... So now
you got to call Ron Moffitino

438
00:23:22.703 --> 00:23:24.105
and tell him you're
ready to give the urn back.

439
00:23:24.238 --> 00:23:26.540
I love it when
you bark orders at me.

440
00:23:27.341 --> 00:23:30.578
- Oh. Mmm. Really?
- Mm-hmm.

441
00:23:31.411 --> 00:23:32.813
Cool.

442
00:23:33.347 --> 00:23:37.285
Mmm. No. but seriously.
get your phone. This is still
an emergency.

443
00:23:37.417 --> 00:23:38.886
Yes. sir.

444
00:23:41.389 --> 00:23:45.458
Seat belt. phone.
Moffitino. Now.

445
00:23:45.593 --> 00:23:48.095
-Mmm.
-Mmm.

446
00:23:50.865 --> 00:23:52.432
-These are the last ones.
-Here. I'll take 'em.

447
00:23:52.566 --> 00:23:54.735
- How many people
did this guy evict?

448
00:23:54.869 --> 00:23:57.605
425 units just
weeks before the murder.

449
00:23:57.738 --> 00:23:59.507
Any word from Amanda?

450
00:23:59.640 --> 00:24:02.243
She's been talking
to the governor.
but I wouldn't count on it.

451
00:24:02.376 --> 00:24:03.978
Let's hit the phones.

452
00:24:04.111 --> 00:24:06.113
All right. we know our suspect
is the boyfriend of a tenant.

453
00:24:06.247 --> 00:24:09.517
so the only names that matter
are women who were single
in 2010.

454
00:24:12.019 --> 00:24:14.655
It's just a numbers game.
We got this.

455
00:24:23.597 --> 00:24:25.166
Okay. we're in business.

456
00:24:25.299 --> 00:24:27.969
Ron's in town and he will meet
us at your place in an hour.

457
00:24:28.836 --> 00:24:31.172
- Why is he in town
if he sent the PI?

458
00:24:31.672 --> 00:24:33.607
Hang on.

459
00:24:34.809 --> 00:24:36.377
You sure
you don't know this guy?

460
00:24:36.510 --> 00:24:38.779
Richie Holgan. the thug? Yeah.
he's my Pilates instructor.

461
00:24:38.913 --> 00:24:40.414
No. How'd you get his wallet?

462
00:24:40.548 --> 00:24:43.918
I grew up with Zach Pansky.
Bad roommate. great thief.

463
00:24:44.051 --> 00:24:48.622
You know. why hire a thug
and a cop to do the same job?

464
00:24:49.390 --> 00:24:51.726
I wonder if there's
another player involved.

465
00:24:51.859 --> 00:24:53.828
Someone else that's interested
in Meat Loaf's ashes.

466
00:24:53.961 --> 00:24:56.597
Shh. This will all
be over in 60 minutes.

467
00:24:57.298 --> 00:24:59.834
Ever had sex in the back
of an autonomous vehicle?

468
00:25:01.402 --> 00:25:03.637
-No. I have not.
-Hmm.

469
00:25:09.276 --> 00:25:10.511
Let's do this.

470
00:25:28.195 --> 00:25:30.631
<i>Attention. riders.</i>

471
00:25:30.765 --> 00:25:34.168
<i>Please return to your own seats</i>
<i>and buckle your safety belts.</i>

472
00:25:35.102 --> 00:25:37.371
-Hello?
<i>-Hi. my name's Mark.</i>

473
00:25:37.506 --> 00:25:40.174
<i>Please return to your own seats</i>
<i>and buckle your safety belts.</i>

474
00:25:40.307 --> 00:25:44.445
Okay. you got it.
Um. sorry about that. Mark.

475
00:25:44.578 --> 00:25:46.515
Don't say sorry. He's a robot.

476
00:25:46.647 --> 00:25:50.017
<i>I'm a vehicle compliance</i>
<i>analyst at a call center</i>
<i>in Tennessee.</i>

477
00:25:50.151 --> 00:25:54.755
<i>and personally.</i>
<i>I find your sexcapades</i>
<i>to be unsavory and indecent.</i>

478
00:25:55.189 --> 00:25:56.991
Excuse me.
we were just kissing.

479
00:25:57.391 --> 00:26:00.261
<i>I know what kissing is. My mom</i>
<i>and dad do it all the time.</i>

480
00:26:01.629 --> 00:26:04.231
-I don't know what
to do with that.
-All right.

481
00:26:05.699 --> 00:26:07.201
Well. now
you don't have to look.

482
00:26:07.334 --> 00:26:08.569
Hmm.

483
00:26:17.278 --> 00:26:19.380
- Mark! What's going on. Mark?
<i>- </i> <i>Get out.</i>

484
00:26:19.514 --> 00:26:22.683
<i>This behavior is a violation</i>
<i>of our terms of service.</i>

485
00:26:22.817 --> 00:26:25.319
What? This is ridiculous.

486
00:26:25.453 --> 00:26:27.188
You know. we didn't
even do anything wrong.

487
00:26:27.321 --> 00:26:30.257
and we're two consenting adults
in a situationship. Mark.

488
00:26:30.391 --> 00:26:32.860
- <i>Get out.</i>
- Whatever. Let's go.

489
00:26:34.495 --> 00:26:36.697
<i>All right. well.</i>
<i>have a blessed day.</i>

490
00:26:37.765 --> 00:26:40.334
- <i>Thank you so much</i>
<i>for riding with us.</i>
-Oh. shut up. Mark.

491
00:26:45.507 --> 00:26:47.708
You know. I have to admit.
I did remove my seat belt.

492
00:26:47.842 --> 00:26:49.310
-Yeah.
-So...

493
00:26:50.177 --> 00:26:52.980
Oh. no. The urn.
it's in the front seat.

494
00:26:53.114 --> 00:26:56.884
-Mark. wait!
-Meat Loaf!

495
00:27:00.488 --> 00:27:01.989
This is why I like a plan.

496
00:27:04.825 --> 00:27:07.294
Hey. hey. listen up.
We got a new lead.

497
00:27:07.428 --> 00:27:09.797
I just spoke to a lady
who remembers someone
named Christine

498
00:27:09.930 --> 00:27:11.398
bragging about
her boyfriend fighting Tom.

499
00:27:11.533 --> 00:27:13.834
No clue about a last name
or a unit number. though.

500
00:27:13.968 --> 00:27:15.836
All right. we're
looking for a Christine!

501
00:27:15.970 --> 00:27:18.873
I'll call Joanne. Maybe
this will help with her appeal.

502
00:27:25.446 --> 00:27:28.182
Thank you. Christine.
I appreciate your time.

503
00:27:28.649 --> 00:27:30.651
Yep. You too. Thanks.

504
00:27:31.485 --> 00:27:33.721
-Any word from the governor?
-Shut down.

505
00:27:33.854 --> 00:27:37.691
No stay unless we can provide
substantial evidence connecting
to a new suspect.

506
00:27:37.825 --> 00:27:39.594
They don't care
that he didn't do it?

507
00:27:39.727 --> 00:27:41.362
They haven't
cared for 15 years.

508
00:27:49.937 --> 00:27:51.438
You ever
witnessed an execution?

509
00:27:52.574 --> 00:27:54.074
I have. yeah.

510
00:27:54.675 --> 00:27:57.512
You know. people used
to think the electric chair
was too brutal.

511
00:27:57.646 --> 00:27:59.648
better to use a needle
like we do with pets.

512
00:27:59.780 --> 00:28:03.184
So two guys got together
and scribbled out the formula
one afternoon.

513
00:28:03.317 --> 00:28:09.790
No research. no nothing.
just back of a napkin. 1977.
in Oklahoma.

514
00:28:09.924 --> 00:28:11.660
It is better. though. right?

515
00:28:11.792 --> 00:28:15.462
I mean. eight out
of ten prisoners drown
in their own blood.

516
00:28:15.597 --> 00:28:17.164
Their lungs literally burn.

517
00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:21.835
Do you know what stays with me?

518
00:28:26.740 --> 00:28:28.709
They give a sedative first.

519
00:28:28.842 --> 00:28:31.212
They have to check to make sure
it works. so someone says
the prisoner's name.

520
00:28:32.146 --> 00:28:34.014
And if there's no response.

521
00:28:34.815 --> 00:28:37.751
they gently stroke
his eyelashes.

522
00:28:39.253 --> 00:28:42.189
I mean. isn't that tender?

523
00:28:43.891 --> 00:28:45.226
It's like...

524
00:28:46.661 --> 00:28:48.762
It's like a butterfly kiss.

525
00:28:50.097 --> 00:28:53.300
These people haven't
been touched in years.

526
00:28:54.802 --> 00:28:56.303
And then they pinch his arm.

527
00:28:57.338 --> 00:28:58.405
George Long.

528
00:28:59.373 --> 00:29:01.942
Eyelash. Arm.

529
00:29:05.346 --> 00:29:07.081
And then they stop his heart.

530
00:29:16.524 --> 00:29:17.559
Three hours.

531
00:29:18.425 --> 00:29:21.362
Found our Christine.
Check out who she's married to.

532
00:29:24.666 --> 00:29:26.367
You think Harris
has sobered up?

533
00:29:28.435 --> 00:29:31.972
I crossed a line. I didn't
know the rules. but now I do.

534
00:29:32.106 --> 00:29:34.509
No. no. They better
not charge you for that ride.

535
00:29:34.643 --> 00:29:36.745
Tell them to give you a refund.
She needs a refund.

536
00:29:36.877 --> 00:29:39.280
I'll never do it again.
You have my word.

537
00:29:40.881 --> 00:29:43.117
Behavior like that
is reserved for the bus.

538
00:29:43.250 --> 00:29:45.219
Yes. you're absolutely right.

539
00:29:45.352 --> 00:29:46.787
Ava. look.

540
00:29:48.322 --> 00:29:51.158
Oh. right. okay.
thank you. Thank you so much.

541
00:29:54.094 --> 00:29:56.297
I can't believe it.

542
00:29:57.699 --> 00:29:59.601
-Five stars.
-Thank you.

543
00:30:02.537 --> 00:30:06.641
No! No. no. no. no. no.
That did not just happen.

544
00:30:06.775 --> 00:30:10.210
It's okay. It's okay. It's
fine. It's really not that bad.

545
00:30:10.344 --> 00:30:15.449
All we need is some superglue
and a carton of cigarettes.

546
00:30:15.583 --> 00:30:18.819
Ash is ash. Nobody
will know the difference.

547
00:30:26.493 --> 00:30:27.494
Whoa.

548
00:30:28.429 --> 00:30:30.464
Now we know why
everyone wants this urn.

549
00:30:41.842 --> 00:30:43.678
Lock the door. Lock it!

550
00:30:43.812 --> 00:30:45.045
Settle down. Ron Moffitino.

551
00:30:45.179 --> 00:30:46.715
-Where's the urn?
-Where's my $1.500?

552
00:30:46.847 --> 00:30:48.650
-I'm a little preoccupied. Ava.
-Give me my damn money. Ron!

553
00:30:48.783 --> 00:30:50.719
-Give me my damn money. Ron!
-You're a thief!
You're a thief!

554
00:30:50.851 --> 00:30:53.555
-I'm a thief? You're a bum!
-Hey! That's enough. okay?

555
00:30:53.688 --> 00:30:56.457
We broke the urn. All right.
I did some research.

556
00:30:56.591 --> 00:30:59.360
Meat Loaf's widow
has his ashes.
and she'd never give 'em up.

557
00:31:00.528 --> 00:31:03.798
-We have the emerald. Ron.
-Give it to me.

558
00:31:04.365 --> 00:31:06.266
I need the emerald or
they're going to kill me.

559
00:31:06.400 --> 00:31:09.604
- Okay. who's gonna
kill you. huh?

560
00:31:10.404 --> 00:31:11.939
This guy?

561
00:31:13.307 --> 00:31:15.710
Start talking. Ron.
or you're gonna go to prison.

562
00:31:15.844 --> 00:31:18.713
How'd you end up with
a stolen gem worth 250 grand?

563
00:31:19.213 --> 00:31:23.384
My friend gave me the
emerald for safekeeping
before he got pinched.

564
00:31:23.518 --> 00:31:25.854
Got myself in a situation
and I needed some cash.

565
00:31:25.986 --> 00:31:27.388
-Evidently.
-Hold on. let him talk.

566
00:31:27.522 --> 00:31:29.056
- Yeah. let me talk.
- Don't push it. Ron.

567
00:31:29.189 --> 00:31:30.357
I'm on her side. all right?

568
00:31:31.358 --> 00:31:34.261
I know this guy Brian.
He deals with this
sort of stuff for the mob.

569
00:31:34.395 --> 00:31:36.196
so we make a plan
for a few days out

570
00:31:36.330 --> 00:31:37.965
and I put the emerald
in the urn for safekeeping.

571
00:31:38.098 --> 00:31:40.802
But then little Miss Sticky
Fingers over here comes along.

572
00:31:40.934 --> 00:31:43.605
All of this could have been
avoided if you just paid me.

573
00:31:44.739 --> 00:31:48.442
I need to give them the emerald
or they're gonna kill me.

574
00:31:52.079 --> 00:31:53.380
Call Brian.

575
00:31:54.248 --> 00:31:55.983
Tell him the deal is on.

576
00:31:58.118 --> 00:31:59.987
Tell me
about your brother.

577
00:32:01.388 --> 00:32:02.423
Pat?

578
00:32:03.792 --> 00:32:06.226
He's a good guy.

579
00:32:07.127 --> 00:32:08.863
-Is he married?
-Yeah.

580
00:32:08.996 --> 00:32:11.900
He and his wife Christine
have been together a long time.

581
00:32:12.433 --> 00:32:16.638
Look. if you want
to save George's life.
you need to tell me the truth.

582
00:32:17.906 --> 00:32:20.441
-I don't know what you mean.
-Come on. Harris.
You can do this.

583
00:32:20.575 --> 00:32:23.477
Christine was evicted.
It wasn't right.

584
00:32:23.611 --> 00:32:25.914
Just so some rich guy
can get a little bit richer.

585
00:32:26.046 --> 00:32:28.348
If I was Pat.
I'd be pissed off too.

586
00:32:30.752 --> 00:32:32.953
Pat was with you
that afternoon. wasn't he?

587
00:32:36.290 --> 00:32:37.958
I can't. I'm sorry. I can't.

588
00:32:38.091 --> 00:32:40.829
Yes. you can. okay? You came
to my office for a reason.

589
00:32:40.961 --> 00:32:45.700
You've spent the last 15
years lying for your brother.

590
00:32:45.834 --> 00:32:49.169
He gets to live his life.
What about you. huh?

591
00:32:50.572 --> 00:32:53.273
I know that this is
ripping you apart inside.

592
00:32:53.407 --> 00:32:55.142
and the only way you
can get rid of that feeling

593
00:32:55.275 --> 00:32:57.044
is if you do this for yourself.

594
00:33:02.517 --> 00:33:04.318
We were driving
to the restaurant.

595
00:33:05.520 --> 00:33:08.255
He said he was fine.
I knew he was lying.

596
00:33:09.289 --> 00:33:12.025
I went in to get food
and I see him...

597
00:33:13.126 --> 00:33:15.162
run into the parking garage.

598
00:33:16.163 --> 00:33:17.565
He had his gun.

599
00:33:20.200 --> 00:33:24.071
- When I heard the shots. I knew it was him.
-  I'm so sorry.

600
00:33:24.204 --> 00:33:25.372
Okay.

601
00:33:25.874 --> 00:33:30.545
Listen. we cannot save George's
life unless we have the gun.

602
00:33:30.678 --> 00:33:34.749
Does your brother still have
it? Do you know where it is?

603
00:33:35.449 --> 00:33:36.250
Uh...

604
00:33:36.885 --> 00:33:39.419
Come on. Harris.
we're running out of time!

605
00:33:40.989 --> 00:33:42.991
It's in his house.

606
00:33:43.123 --> 00:33:46.360
-Behind the fridge.
-Yes. Yes.

607
00:33:50.497 --> 00:33:53.066
- APD! Patrick Weber. hands up!
- What's going on?

608
00:33:53.200 --> 00:33:54.468
-Get out of my house!
-Let's go!

609
00:33:54.602 --> 00:33:55.937
-We have a warrant. Sit down.
-For what?

610
00:33:56.069 --> 00:33:57.672
Let me see your hands.
Let's go.

611
00:33:57.805 --> 00:33:59.574
- Whoa.
- All right.
Hands up. Christine.

612
00:33:59.707 --> 00:34:01.543
-Okay. okay!
-We are good. we are good here.

613
00:34:01.676 --> 00:34:04.012
- What's this about?
 Hey. there's-- -Hands up!

614
00:34:04.144 --> 00:34:06.246
-What is going on?
-I don't know.
Don't worry about it.

615
00:34:06.380 --> 00:34:08.248
-What are they doing here?
-I don't know!

616
00:34:08.382 --> 00:34:09.851
Mitchell! How's it going
in there. Mitchell?

617
00:34:09.984 --> 00:34:12.520
I'm good! I found the gun.
It was behind the fridge.

618
00:34:12.654 --> 00:34:14.923
That's not mine!
I want a lawyer!

619
00:34:15.088 --> 00:34:18.960
You can have one. You are
under arrest for the murders
of Tom and Marjorie Kelly.

620
00:34:19.092 --> 00:34:20.427
No!

621
00:34:27.735 --> 00:34:28.903
Where's Ron?

622
00:34:29.037 --> 00:34:32.306
Don't worry about Ron.
I'm the guy with the jewel.

623
00:34:35.877 --> 00:34:37.144
You look good. milkshake.

624
00:34:38.345 --> 00:34:40.213
My associate
doesn't like you very much.

625
00:34:40.347 --> 00:34:42.984
Your associate's
been a real pain in my ass.

626
00:34:43.116 --> 00:34:45.319
In fact. I should
charge you an extra 50 grand.

627
00:34:45.452 --> 00:34:47.055
Ron and I agreed on a price.

628
00:34:47.187 --> 00:34:49.156
That's right.

629
00:34:49.289 --> 00:34:51.491
Then why'd you send extra
strong hot dog bun over here
to steal it first?

630
00:34:52.159 --> 00:34:55.863
I don't trust you. Brian.
and I have other offers.

631
00:34:56.798 --> 00:34:58.265
You have the money?

632
00:35:06.440 --> 00:35:08.141
I want to see the emerald.

633
00:35:09.376 --> 00:35:11.211
Step right into my office.

634
00:35:21.789 --> 00:35:22.824
We good?

635
00:35:23.992 --> 00:35:26.226
Pushy. pushy.

636
00:35:28.462 --> 00:35:29.831
Do we have a deal?

637
00:35:31.365 --> 00:35:32.634
No.

638
00:35:33.835 --> 00:35:35.302
I'm taking it for free.

639
00:35:36.537 --> 00:35:39.406
-Kill this idiot.
-Hang on. Hey. hang on.

640
00:35:41.241 --> 00:35:43.176
-You a fan of Meat Loaf?
-What?

641
00:35:43.611 --> 00:35:44.746
Meat Loaf. the singer.

642
00:35:44.879 --> 00:35:46.380
- On the ground!
- GBI!

643
00:35:46.514 --> 00:35:48.850
Put your weapons down!

644
00:35:50.317 --> 00:35:51.586
Drop 'em!

645
00:35:53.988 --> 00:35:55.355
Do not move!

646
00:35:57.491 --> 00:36:00.394
You're under arrest. idiot.

647
00:36:02.630 --> 00:36:04.899
<i>The governor has yet to</i>
<i>comment on the execution.</i>

648
00:36:05.033 --> 00:36:07.401
We have less than an hour. Why
are they dragging their feet?

649
00:36:07.535 --> 00:36:10.104
They have the power.
They can do whatever they want.

650
00:36:10.237 --> 00:36:11.539
Either way. we did good work.

651
00:36:11.673 --> 00:36:13.841
Either way?
What's that supposed to mean?

652
00:36:13.975 --> 00:36:15.710
It means it's out of our hands.

653
00:36:15.843 --> 00:36:17.712
<i>Long appears</i>
<i>to be out of options...</i>

654
00:36:19.814 --> 00:36:22.315
<i>...and is hoping</i>
<i>for a last-minute miracle</i>
<i>to avoid being executed.</i>

655
00:36:22.449 --> 00:36:23.450
I need to take this.

656
00:36:23.584 --> 00:36:25.119
Is it the governor? Joanne?

657
00:36:25.252 --> 00:36:27.487
<i>...and</i>
<i>despite his best efforts</i>

658
00:36:27.622 --> 00:36:30.958
<i>it looks like George Long</i>
<i>is running out of time.</i>

659
00:36:31.092 --> 00:36:32.994
<i>There's no</i>
<i>change in status right now...</i>

660
00:36:33.127 --> 00:36:35.830
- I know you don't need
to hear this...

661
00:36:35.963 --> 00:36:37.098
...but I'm proud of you.

662
00:36:57.952 --> 00:36:59.954
They reopened the case
against Pat.

663
00:37:02.255 --> 00:37:03.591
We got a stay.

664
00:37:05.193 --> 00:37:06.694
George will get to come home.

665
00:37:29.150 --> 00:37:32.553
Most people do coffee in
the morning. You rearrange.

666
00:37:32.687 --> 00:37:34.889
Just keeping you
on your toes.

667
00:37:35.656 --> 00:37:38.993
What do you think? Really
opens the room up. right?

668
00:37:42.029 --> 00:37:45.032
Um... Yeah. Wide open.

669
00:37:47.501 --> 00:37:48.736
Wild night. huh?

670
00:37:48.870 --> 00:37:52.106
Oh. my.
How do you live like this?

671
00:37:52.240 --> 00:37:54.542
I don't know.

672
00:37:55.143 --> 00:37:56.210
You made it look pretty easy.

673
00:38:00.047 --> 00:38:02.984
I should probably go.
I head to Portugal tomorrow.

674
00:38:03.117 --> 00:38:04.185
Mmm.

675
00:38:04.317 --> 00:38:06.020
-How long?
-Just a few weeks.

676
00:38:06.453 --> 00:38:10.925
Great. Just enough time
for my heart rate
to get back to normal.

677
00:38:12.193 --> 00:38:13.426
I'll call you.

678
00:38:13.928 --> 00:38:15.395
Will you?

679
00:38:15.530 --> 00:38:19.466
I am responsible
and conscientious.
and I do like a plan.

680
00:38:19.600 --> 00:38:22.069
But I also like this.

681
00:38:23.271 --> 00:38:26.574
- It's fun.
And a little dangerous.
- Mmm.

682
00:38:27.074 --> 00:38:28.876
So. yeah. I will call you.

683
00:38:32.013 --> 00:38:33.080
Okay.

684
00:38:34.582 --> 00:38:35.716
Oh. damn it.

685
00:38:36.416 --> 00:38:39.319
Would you call me a car?
They've suspended my account.

686
00:38:39.452 --> 00:38:43.658
Ooh. You know. I'd
do anything for love. but...

687
00:38:44.625 --> 00:38:46.060
I won't do that.

688
00:38:47.762 --> 00:38:49.462
-Let me drive you home.
-Okay.

689
00:39:08.716 --> 00:39:10.383
-Oh. thank you.
-Thank you.

690
00:39:10.518 --> 00:39:11.819
-Enjoy.
-All right.

691
00:39:12.787 --> 00:39:17.258
Oh. no. too sweet.
No. This-- This is better.

692
00:39:17.825 --> 00:39:20.094
Oh. Yeah.
What was I even thinking?

693
00:39:20.228 --> 00:39:23.731
Here I am grabbing pancake
syrup when I should've been
grabbing pancake jelly.

694
00:39:23.865 --> 00:39:25.733
Who doesn't love pancake jelly?

695
00:39:25.867 --> 00:39:27.235
Oh. boy.

696
00:39:27.367 --> 00:39:28.603
Try it.

697
00:39:34.342 --> 00:39:36.944
You're just changing lives
left and right. huh?

698
00:39:37.078 --> 00:39:38.546
Well. someone has to.

699
00:39:38.679 --> 00:39:41.916
Yeah. but they don't. You care.

700
00:39:43.684 --> 00:39:45.052
That's the job.

701
00:39:47.855 --> 00:39:51.192
You know. when
I first started with the APD.

702
00:39:51.325 --> 00:39:54.028
it was guys like Pyzeck
who took me under their wings.

703
00:39:55.062 --> 00:39:57.064
And I thought
they had it all figured out.

704
00:39:57.598 --> 00:40:01.434
You solve a case.
you kill a fifth.
you do it again the next day.

705
00:40:01.569 --> 00:40:04.906
You never get attached.
you never bring it home.
you just...

706
00:40:06.173 --> 00:40:07.875
keep moving forward.

707
00:40:09.710 --> 00:40:11.045
It took me all these years
to figure out

708
00:40:11.178 --> 00:40:12.980
that you don't do that
because you're strong.

709
00:40:13.748 --> 00:40:15.783
You don't do that
'cause you're tough.

